1. List images already available on your system
docker images

2. Pull the latest Ubuntu image
docker pull ubuntu:latest

3. Run a container using the Ubuntu image
docker run -it --name ubuntu-test ubuntu:latest 

4. Try to remove the Ubuntu image
docker rmi ubuntu:latest

5. Check all containers, including stopped ones
docker ps -a

6. Remove the container that uses the image
docker rm ubuntu-test

7. Remove the Ubuntu image again
docker rmi ubuntu:latest
